-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Kenya Airways, SG-SSB Ghana Active
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-04-02T16:07:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-kenya-airways-total-kenya-are-active.html
Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  fell for
the first time in 10 days, declining 0.5 percent to 1,796.96 by
the end of trading.  Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  slipped 0.3 percent to 59.61 in
Nairobi. The  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  rose for the second day,
climbing 1.2 percent to 898.55 in Windhoek. The  Nigerian Stock
Exchange All-Share Index (NGSEINDX)  was little changed at 20,650.95 in
Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement from the bourse.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Kenya Airways Ltd. (KNAL)  , sub-Saharan Africa’s third-
biggest airline, gained as much as 1.8 percent, before trading
0.4 percent higher at 14 shillings, the first increase in three
days, as it began a rights offer to investors aimed at raising
$250 million.  SG-SSB Ltd. (SGSSB)  , the Ghanaian unit of Societe
Generale SA, jumped 2.3 percent to 45 pesewas, the highest since
March 23, after saying it will grow loans by as much as 22
percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
